  "text": "Let us define Dwyer-Kan equivalences: In particular, every Quillen equivalence of model categories gives rise to a DwyerKan equivalence of their simplicial localizations. According to [CITATION_1] , there exists a model category structure on the category of (small) simplicial categories with the Dwyer-Kan equivalences as weak equivalences. Since every simplicial category is Dwyer-Kan equivalent to the simplicial localization of a certain relative category, this model structure forms a homotopy theory of homotopy theories.",
